This paper deals with the detection of anomalies in online social networks, which is a major concern in the field of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed approach uses a combination of neural networks and fuzzy logic, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The approach also involves the use of data analysis and processing techniques, which can be categorized under the subfield of data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of large datasets, which is a common theme in the subfield of social informatics (cs.SI).
